Try some of these:
&quot;The Moral Animal&quot;, Robert Wright
&quot;Unto Others&quot;, Sobor and Wilson
&quot;The Red Queen&quot;, Ridley

There are many more.  One way to find them is to follow links in the
Amazon reviews.

I think it is also important to understand just what you (and everyone else)
means when they talk about 'morality'.  So it might be a good idea to
read something more along the lines of what philosophers say about
'Ethics', rather than what evolutionary psychologists say about morality.

Take a look at modern philosophical 'social contract' theorists like
Nozick or Rawls.  Ask yourself just how universal such a contract
should be in evolutionary thinking.  Then look at some of the stuff
that has been done in evolutionary game theory - especially the
'Tit for Tat' simulations that grew out of the research of Axelrod
and Hamilton.

It is a very big subject.
