state.  Humans don't have a lock on that emotion and it has been
demonstrated in other species.  If empathy is the ability to consider the
emotional state of another of your species it would serve as a biological
basis for the social evolution of morality as a cultural phenomenon.  In a
psychological sense sociopaths have no empathy
